Sanjay is Sanskrit for Victor and/or Protector. It is a common first name in India, and among Indian diaspora. The name is sometimes confused with Sanjaya, a character from the Hindu epic Mahabharata.

"Sanjay" is the name of a young Indian immigrant on the American animated television series The Fairly OddParents

